led somewhere else
another monk, a nun
a medieval abbess
a Benedictine
of his own order
of his own tradition
also canonized by a Benedict
the recent one

---

12th century
given to a monastery
at eight
as a tenth
not chosen
given
the way daughters were given
when there were too many

had visions from childhood
nobody knew what to do with that

---

she saw it
a rhythm
after years of visions
in Rhine the Valley
when the river flooded
when the silt stayed
when the vines grew

viriditas
the greening
a living force
runs through everything alive

the one who gives
also the one who leaves

ariditas
the dark sister
what sets in at the edges
before the center knows

---

she watched both
in bodies
in communities
in the land around her

the sequence was always the same

the edges go quiet first
the center still looks stable
by the time the center feels it —
the edges are already dry

---

she tried to green the gray

with no institutional voice
the institution had a place for obedience
for silence
for prayer at the prescribed hours

it had no place for what she carried

---

so she said she couldn't speak

called herself unlearned
incapable
only a mere messenger
a feather on the breath of God

not a scholar
not a theologian
not an authority

---

that was the gap

the institution could silence a scholar
could redirect a theologian
could contain an authority

it had no mechanism
for silencing a vision

she moved through the one opening
it couldn't close

---

what came through:

medicine
music
cosmology
natural science
governance philosophy
letters to emperors
letters to popes
corrections of bishops
four preaching tours
when women didn't preach

all of it
from someone
who claimed she couldn't speak

---

the institution tried to contain her anyway

reassigned her closest companion
to another convent
to break the transmission

the church silenced her community
forbade them from singing

she fought it
until the interdict lifted

they sang again

---

the knowledge traveled anyway

through the nuns who stayed
through the manuscripts that moved
through the pilgrims who came
through letters crossing Europe
faster than any institution could track

the Benedictine nuns of Eibingen
are still singing her compositions
in 2026

847 years of unbroken transmission
through bodies
not buildings

---

the institution didn't preserve that

the transmission survived
because it moved through relationships
the institution couldn't fully control

---

the knowledge that survives
is always the knowledge
that already traveled

not because anyone planned the fire

because someone understood
that living in one place
is living at risk

---

the ones who carry without claiming
move through gaps
the structure can't close

not because they're weak

because the structure has no mechanism
for what doesn't announce itself

---

that's not a workaround

that's the only thing
that has ever survived
everything thrown at it

